comments: Plumlee (CHA) establishes himself in Brunson's (NYK) path and is firming up when he absorbs the marginal contact.
Plumlee (CHA) establishes himself in Barrett's (NYK) path and he absorbs the contact during the pick.
Robinson (NYK) reaches in with his left arm and avoids making contact with Oubre Jr.'s (CHA) right arm after his gather during the driving shot attempt.
Reddish (NYK) contests the driving shot attempt and incidental "high-five" contact occurs with Oubre Jr. (CHA) after the release.
Robinson (NYK) establishes himself in Smith Jr.?s (CHA) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Smith Jr. (CHA) legally contests Brunson's (NYK) jump shot attempt.
Plumlee (CHA) establishes himself in Brunson's (NYK) path and incidental contact occurs when Brunson goes under the pick.
Barrett (NYK) extends his forearm to Hayward's (CHA) front and contact occurs that affects Hayward's SQBR during his drive.
Barrett (NYK) contests the jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Hayward?s (CHA) arm after the release.
Plumlee (CHA) moves laterally into Brunson's (NYK) path and initiates body contact that affects Brunson's (NYK) SQBR during the drive.
Brunson's (NYK) right foot reestablishes position in inbounds prior to receiving the ball.
Washington (CHA) legally contests Brunson's (NYK) jump shot attempt.
Plumlee (CHA) and Robinson (NYK) mutually engage and disengage during the rebounding opportunity and the contact is marginal.
Randle (NYK) moves towards the basket with his left arm extended outwards and marginal contact occurs with Smith Jr. (CHA) during the rebounding opportunity.
Smith Jr. (CHA) avoids making contact with Randle's (NYK) arm when he swipes down during Randle's shot attempt near the rim.
Plumlee (CHA) establishes himself in Reddish's (NYK) path and marginal contact occurs when Reddish fights through the screen.
Plumlee (CHA) establishes himself in Barrett?s (NYK) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Brunson (NYK) is retreating his arm into a vertical position and absorbs the marginal contact that occurs with Smith Jr. (CHA) after his gather.
Washington's (CHA) arm is retreating into a vertical position when marginal contact occurs with Randle's (NYK) off-arm  during the driving shot attempt.
Plumlee (CHA) establishes himself in Barrett's (NYK) path and marginal contact occurs as the players disengage after the screen.
Washington (CHA) establishes himself in Barrett's (NYK) path and does not deliver illegal contact while setting the screen.
Oubre Jr. (CHA) briefly places his left arm on Reddish's (NYK) side and marginal contact occurs as he releases away from the defender.
Randle (NYK) places a resting forearm on Hayward's (CHA) body and marginal contact occurs during Hayward's driving shot attempt.
Robinson (NYK) contests the driving shot attempt and marginal body contact occurs with Hayward (CHA) after the release.
Washington (CHA) jumps from point A to point B and initiates contact with Randle (NYK), which affects his driving shot attempt.
Hayward (CHA) makes contact with Robinson's (NYK) right arm as he attempts to secure the loose ball. The contact to Robinson's arm impacts his ability to control the rebound.
Plumlee (CHA) and Brunson (NYK) come together at the same spot on the floor and marginal contact occurs during the play in transition.
Reddish (NYK) initiates contact with Washington's (CHA) arm, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Washington (CHA) momentarily places a resting hand on Randle's (NYK) body, and the contact is marginal as the players disengage after Randle rolls to the basket.
Smith Jr. (CHA) legally contests Barrett's (NYK) jump shot attempt.
Hayward (CHA) brushes Barrett's (NYK) off-arm, and marginal contact occurs during Barrett's shot attempt near the rim.
Hayward (CHA) makes marginal contact with Randle's (NYK) right arm and Randle is able to secure the rebound through the marginal contact.

Plumlee (CHA) lowers his left hand down and makes contact with the ball that dislodges it from Randle (NYK) as he starts to power up towards the basket. Any subsequent arm contact is considered incidental.

Washington (CHA) and Randle (NYK) go to the ground in pursuit of the loose ball and the contact during the pursuit is marginal. Once on the ground, Washington extends his arm into the ball and dislodges it from Randle's grasp.
Reddish (NYK) and Oubre Jr. (CHA) come together on the same spot on the floor and marginal contact occurs in pursuit of the loose ball.
Randle (NYK) legally contests Washington's (CHA) jump shot attempt.
Plumlee (CHA) commits a take foul on Robinson (NYK). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Randle (NYK) is firming up on his left foot when Oubre Jr. (CHA) fights over the screen and marginal contact occurs.
Robinson's (NYK) arms come out slightly as he sets the screen on Washington (CHA) and the ensuing contact is marginal.
Randle (NYK) is firming up on his left foot and marginal contact occurs as Smith Jr. (CHA) moves into the pick.
Hayward (CHA) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently exiting.
Smith Jr. (CHA) legally contests Brunson's (NYK) jump shot attempt.
Oubre Jr. (CHA) establishes himself in Randle's (NYK) path and does not deliver illegal contact while setting the screen.
Oubre Jr. (CHA) establishes his right foot as his pivot foot and then lifts and re-plants that foot at the start of his dribble.

Barrett (NYK) is retreating his right arm to a vertical position when some marginal head contact occurs with Oubre Jr. (CHA). Contact to an opponent?s head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Washington (CHA) lowers his right arm down and marginal contact occurs with Randle's (NYK) off-arm as he takes it off of the ball during the driving shot attempt.
Washington (CHA) establishes himself in Reddish's (NYK) path and his legs remain within the frame of his body as contact occurs, which he does not deliver.
Plumlee (CHA) is firming up on his right foot when Reddish (NYK) fights through the screen and marginal contact occurs.
Reddish (NYK) legally contests Oubre Jr.'s  (CHA) jump shot attempt.
Oubre Jr. (CHA) establishes himself in Barrett's (NYK) path and marginal contact occurs as Barret fights over the top of the screen.
Randle (NYK) makes last contact with the ball before it bounces out of bounds. Possession is properly retained by Charlotte.
Robinson (NYK) gets to ball height and cleanly blocks McDaniels' (CHA) driving shot attempt.
Barrett (NYK) extends his arm into Oubre Jr.'s (CHA) path, causing both players to briefly engage and separate off-ball.
Oubre Jr. (CHA) brings his right arm up to Barret's (NYK) fronting arm and the contact is marginal as the two players engage during the screen.
Washington (CHA) is firming up on his left foot when Reddish (NYK) navigates over the top of it and marginal contact occurs.
Hayward (CHA) and Reddish (NYK) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs as the screen is set.
Reddish (NYK) legally contests Washington's (CHA) jump shot attempt.
Replay review shows Washington's (CHA) right foot is on the three-point arc during the release of the jump shot.
Quickley (NYK) establishes himself in McDaniels' (CHA) path and marginal contact occurs as Quickley is firming up.
Quickley (NYK) firms up on his right leg and marginal contact occurs as Oubre Jr. (CHA) fights through the screen.
Oubre Jr. (CHA) commits a take foul on Barrett (NYK). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Randle (NYK) commits a take foul on Smith Jr. (CHA). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Washington (CHA) lowers his arm down and makes some contact with the ball but is not able to dislodge it from Barrett (NYK). The arm contact on the play is marginal.
